// "description": "<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>Aim of the Course</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To train nurses of the Association currently working in the operating theatre for achieving a high quality and specialized patient care</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To develop theatre nurse to be more competent in their roles and responsibilities</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><u>Target Participants</u></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nurses currently working in Operating Rooms or Sterile Supply Service, and who are active members of the Association of Hong Kong Operating Room Nurses Limited.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Schedule of the Course</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Certificate Course in Peri-operative Nursing (Class 17)</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>08</strong><strong>.10.20</strong><strong>21</strong><strong> – 10.12.20</strong><strong>21</strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"type\":\"1\"} -->\n<ol type=\"1\"><li>Lectures:</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Nine lecture sessions of 2 hours each at 6:30 – 8:30 pm on Friday are:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>Day 1 - <span class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\">10.12.2021</span></strong></td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>Day 2 - 15.10.2021</strong></td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>Day 3 - 22.10.2021</strong></td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>Day 4 - 29.10.2021</strong></td></tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>Day 5 -</strong> <strong>05.11.2021</strong></td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>Day 6 - 12.11.2021</strong></td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>Day 7 - 19.11.2021</strong></td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>Day 8 - 26.11.2021</strong></td></tr><tr><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>Day 9 - 03.12.2021</strong></td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td><td class=\"has-text-align-center\" data-align=\"center\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Examination &amp; Course Evaluation:</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><span class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\">17.12.2021</span></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:table -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong><u>Fee </u></strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td><td><strong>HK $ 2,000 </strong>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td><strong><u>Size of Class</u></strong><strong></strong></td><td>40-60 participants &nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td><strong><u>Venue</u></strong><strong></strong></td><td>CUHK Medical Centre 9 Chak Cheung Street, Shatin, New Territories, Hong Kong (<span class=\"has-inline-color has-black-color\">May conduct in zoom if pandemic situation of COVID-19 persist) </span><span class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-red-color\">&nbsp;</span></td></tr><tr><td><strong><u>C</u></strong><strong><u>ours</u></strong><strong><u>e Coordinator</u></strong><strong></strong></td><td>Ms. Cindy YIP, Academic Convenor, &nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td><strong><u>Language Medium</u></strong><strong></strong></td><td>Both English and Cantonese will be used.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Examination will be conducted in English &nbsp;</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>\n<!-- /wp:table -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><u>Course Contents</u></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"type\":\"1\"} -->\n<ol type=\"1\"><li>Concepts of Peri-operative nursing / Organization of the OR Team</li><li>OT design &amp; environment</li><li>Scrubbing, gowning &amp; gloving and Draping,</li><li>Counting of accountable items</li><li>Incision, wound closure and healing</li><li>Care and handling of specimens</li><li>Surgical positioning</li><li>Care and handling of basic surgical and powered instruments</li><li>Surgical Suturing and staplers</li><li>Intubation equipment and procedure &amp; intraoperative physiological monitoring</li><li>Care and handling of energy modality equipment</li><li>Introduction to Minimal invasive surgery</li><li>Infection control in the OR</li><li>Sterilization and disinfection in OR</li><li>Handling Crisis in OR</li><li>Safety and Quality Improvement in OR</li><li>Introduction to Anaesthesia</li><li>Recovery Room Nursing</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Award of Certificate/ CNE</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"type\":\"1\"} -->\n<ol type=\"1\"><li>Achievement certificate will be awarded to those with attendance not less than 7 sessions (excluding examination session), and passing score of 60% in a written examination.&nbsp;</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Attendance certificate will be issued to participants achieving not less than 7 (excluding examination session) sessions of class attendance but failed in the written examination.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Two CNE permits from Hong Kong Nursing Council will be awarded to participants who attended each session.&nbsp; Maximum 18 CNE points will be awarded in this programme.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><u>Remarks:</u></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true,\"type\":\"1\"} -->\n<ol type=\"1\"><li>No class will be held on public holidays and when typhoon signal No. 8 or above, or the Black Rainstorm Warning Signal is hoisted before the commencement of the class.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Class will be held as usual only if the typhoon signal No. 8 or above, or the &nbsp;&nbsp;Black Rainstorm Warning Signal is lowered before 15:00 hours on that day.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\"><strong>Application Information</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Applicants must be <strong>active members of HKORN, RN/EN</strong> currently working in Operating Room.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong><u>Deadline of application: 31 August 2021</u></strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n[restrict userlevel=\"subscriber\"]<h2 class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>Application Form</strong></h2>[/restrict]\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[restrict userlevel=\"subscriber\"][contact-form-7 id=\"6821\" title=\"Contact form 1\"][/restrict]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->",
